8. The real current state of your workflow

Right now, your workflow is best thought of as:

Already built

prompt architecture

scoring architecture

batch architecture

A/B testing architecture

repo structure


Not yet fully wired

real LLM client integration

automatic planner → generator chaining

automatic saving/loading of generated outputs from a live model


So today, the practical way to run it is:

Option A — manual but real

Use your prompt files directly in ChatGPT / Claude / your add-in / your repo workflow.

Option B — scripted but partly simulated

Run the Python scripts with the dummy client to test wiring.

Option C — next real upgrade

Connect the scripts to an actual model endpoint.


